Cycling {1} ({1}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
cards.flavor: Remarkably, dinner continued with no further interruptions.

cards.name: Steelgaze Griffin
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever you draw your second card each turn, Steelgaze Griffin gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"If we didn't guard our secrets, they wouldn't remain secrets for long."
-Gadwick, the Wizened

cards.name: Stinging Lionfish
cards.text: Whenever you cast your first spell during each opponent's turn, you may tap or untap target nonland permanent.
cards.flavor: Starfish are its favorite prey.

cards.name: Stolen by the Fae
cards.text: Return target creature with mana value X to its owner's hand. You create X 1/1 blue Faerie creature tokens with flying.
cards.flavor: Denizens of the wilds don't always seek to harm intruders. Sometimes they simply misplace them.

cards.name: Stonybrook Angler
cards.text: {1}{U}, {T}: You may tap or untap target creature.
cards.flavor: "Water is in the air, the trees, and the earth. Understand its motion, speak its language, and the subtle currents that flow through all living things will fall under your command."

cards.name: Storm Sculptor
cards.text:
Storm Sculptor can't be blocked.
When Storm Sculptor enters the battlefield, return a creature you control to its owner's hand.
cards.flavor: In his hands, the wind can become a weapon or a means of escape.

Whenever Svyelun attacks, draw a card.

cards.text:
Syr Elenora, the Discerning's power is equal to the number of cards in your hand.

cards.name: Tamiyo, the Moon Sage
cards.text:
[+1]: Tap target permanent. It doesn't untap during its controller's next untap step.
[−2]: Draw a card for each tapped creature target player controls.
[−8]: You get an emblem with "You have no maximum hand size" and "Whenever a card is put into your graveyard from anywhere, you may return it to your hand."

cards.name: Teferi's Protege
cards.text: {1}{U}, {T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
cards.flavor: Teferi's legacy lives on in Tolaria through the study of time magic and a tradition of irrepressible mischief.

cards.name: Tezzeret, Artifice Master
cards.text:
[+1]: Create a 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature token with flying.
[0]: Draw a card. If you control three or more artifacts, draw two cards instead.

cards.name: Thopter Spy Network
cards.text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, if you control an artifact, create a 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature token with flying.
Whenever one or more artifact creatures you control deal combat damage to a player, draw a card.

cards.name: Tolarian Kraken
cards.text: Whenever you draw a card, you may pay {1}. When you do, you may tap or untap target creature.
cards.flavor:
"It's contemplative, resourceful, and original. Everything else aside, it's the perfect student."
-Naban, dean of iteration

cards.name: Tolarian Sentinel
cards.text:
Flying
{U}, {T}, Discard a card: Return target permanent you control to its owner's hand.
cards.flavor: "It is not just our people I try to rescue. It is our culture, and our hope that we can return to greatness."

cards.name: Tome Anima
cards.text: Tome Anima can't be blocked as long as you've drawn two or more cards this turn.
cards.flavor: Sometimes knowledge takes on a life of its own.

cards.name: Triton Shorestalker
cards.text: Triton Shorestalker can't be blocked.
cards.flavor: "Who will miss you, drywalker? A wife? A child? Perhaps they will blame the sea for your fate, and teach future generations to stay far away from it."

cards.name: Undersea Invader
cards.text:
Flash
Undersea Invader enters the battlefield tapped.
cards.flavor:
"The currents are strange today, and the fish are fearful. Something's stirring in the depths."
-Rathstaf, Kannah fisherman

cards.name: Vedalken Engineer
cards.text: {T}: Add two mana of any one color. Spend this mana only to cast artifact spells or activate abilities of artifacts.
cards.flavor: Art is unknown to the vedalken-for them, all creations must serve a purpose.

cards.name: Vendilion Clique
cards.text:
Flash
Flying
When Vendilion Clique enters the battlefield, look at target player's hand. You may choose a nonland card from it. If you do, that player reveals the chosen card, puts it on the bottom of their library, then draws a card.

cards.name: Wake Thrasher
cards.text: Whenever a permanent you control becomes untapped, Wake Thrasher gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Anyone who thinks merrows have more brains than brawn has never been run over by one.

cards.name: Watertrap Weaver
cards.text: When Watertrap Weaver enters the battlefield, tap target creature an opponent controls. That creature doesn't untap during its controller's next untap step.
cards.flavor: The river is a powerful friend.

cards.name: Wavebreak Hippocamp
cards.text: Whenever you cast your first spell during each opponent's turn, draw a card.
cards.flavor: Tritons search for omens in its wake.

cards.name: Weldfast Wingsmith
cards.text: Whenever an artifact enters the battlefield under your control, Weldfast Wingsmith gains flying until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "Airships are too confining. If I'm in the sky, I want to feel the wind in my hair and taste the aether."

cards.name: Windrider Patrol
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever Windrider Patrol deals combat damage to a player, scry 2. (Look at the top two cards of your library, then put any number of them on the bottom of your library and the rest on top in any order.)

cards.name: Winter's Rest
cards.text:
Enchant creature
When Winter's Rest enters the battlefield, tap enchanted creature.
As long as you control another snow permanent, enchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.

cards.name: Alley Strangler
cards.text: Menace
cards.flavor: "You never know what day might be your last."

cards.name: Ancient Craving
cards.text: You draw three cards and you lose 3 life.
cards.flavor: Knowledge demands sacrifice.

cards.name: Black Cat
cards.text: When Black Cat dies, target opponent discards a card at random.
cards.flavor: Its last life is spent tormenting your dreams.

cards.name: Blight Keeper
cards.text:
Flying
{7}{B}, {T}, Sacrifice Blight Keeper: Target opponent loses 4 life and you gain 4 life.
cards.flavor: It withers fruit and flesh alike.

cards.name: Blood Price
cards.text: Look at the top four cards of your library. Put two of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order. You lose 2 life.
cards.flavor: Blood is the oldest currency.

cards.name: Bloodbond Vampire
cards.text: Whenever you gain life, put a +1/+1 counter on Bloodbond Vampire.
cards.flavor:
"Let the vampires join us. In this war, we no longer have the luxury of choosing our comrades."
-General Tazri, allied commander

cards.name: Bloodthirsty Aerialist
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever you gain life, put a +1/+1 counter on Bloodthirsty Aerialist.
cards.flavor: A circus acrobat in life, she kills with such fluid grace that even her victims are awed by her performance.

cards.name: Bloodtracker
cards.text:
Flying
{B}, Pay 2 life: Put a +1/+1 counter on Bloodtracker.
When Bloodtracker leaves the battlefield, draw a card for each +1/+1 counter on it.
cards.flavor: "Flee all you like. The further you run the more firmly I feel your heartbeat."

cards.name: Bone Picker
cards.text:
This spell costs {3} less to cast if a creature died this turn.
Flying, deathtouch
cards.flavor: They are the first to greet dissenters on their journey into exile.

cards.name: Burglar Rat
cards.text: When Burglar Rat enters the battlefield, each opponent discards a card.
cards.flavor:
"Even rats hoard their treasures. Are your precious things so different?"
-Izoni

cards.name: Cemetery Recruitment
cards.text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand. If it's a Zombie card, draw a card.
cards.flavor: "There's a smoothness to my magic here that I don't find on any other plane."

cards.name: Certain Death
cards.text: Destroy target creature. Its controller loses 2 life and you gain 2 life.
cards.flavor: Some spirits cling to one person, feasting on the growing fear until a final moment of all-consuming terror.

cards.name: Chittering Rats
cards.text: When Chittering Rats enters the battlefield, target opponent puts a card from their hand on top of their library.
cards.flavor: Bottom feeders sometimes rise to the top.

cards.name: Consign to the Pit
cards.text: Destroy target creature. Consign to the Pit deals 2 damage to that creature's controller.
cards.flavor: First your whole life flashes before your eyes. Then you have considerable time to reflect on every regret as you plummet.

cards.name: Corpse Churn
cards.text: Mill three cards, then you may return a creature card from your graveyard to your hand. (To mill a card, put the top card of your library into your graveyard.)
cards.flavor:
"The distraction of your life has ended. Now your service begins."
-Kalitas, thrall of Ulamog

cards.name: Crow of Dark Tidings
cards.text:
Flying
When Crow of Dark Tidings enters the battlefield or dies, mill two cards. (Put the top two cards of your library into your graveyard.)
cards.flavor:
"Well, this can't be a good sign."
-Old Rutstein

cards.name: Cruel Sadist
cards.text:
{B}, {T}, Pay 1 life: Put a +1/+1 counter on Cruel Sadist.
{2}{B}, {T}, Remove X +1/+1 counters from Cruel Sadist: It deals X damage to target creature.
cards.flavor: Face of innocence. Hand of death. Designed by Edmund McMillen

cards.name: Crypt Rats
cards.text: {X}: Crypt Rats deals X damage to each creature and each player. Spend only black mana on X.
cards.flavor:
"Shoo, you little worm tails-go away! My corpses aren't your dinner!"
-Ghoulcaller Gisa

cards.name: Dead Weight
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets -2/-2.
cards.flavor: All things considered, his first day on patrol could have gone better.

cards.name: Death Wind
cards.text: Target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"I am a dragonslayer for Lord Silumgar. There is no dragon save him whom I fear."
-Xathi the Infallible

cards.name: Deathbloom Thallid
cards.text: When Deathbloom Thallid dies, create a 1/1 green Saproling creature token.
cards.flavor:
"Nature is not always gentle or kind, but all life begets life."
-Marwyn of Llanowar

cards.name: Deathbringer Regent
cards.text:
Flying

cards.name: Demon of Catastrophes
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Flying, trample
cards.flavor: A pit yawned open, a column of oily smoke arose, and a towering form hissed, "I accept this offering."

cards.name: Demonic Gifts
cards.text: Until end of turn, target creature gets +2/+0 and gains "When this creature dies, return it to the battlefield under its owner's control."
cards.flavor: It began as a flavor on the tongue, like a bloody morsel of roast boar-but soon the power was a conflagration in her veins.

cards.name: Demon's Disciple
cards.text: When Demon's Disciple enters the battlefield, each player sacrifices a creature or planeswalker.
cards.flavor: Taborax's cultists are the latest in a long history of beings who have desired to see Zendikar torn to pieces.

cards.name: Demon's Grasp
cards.text: Target creature gets -5/-5 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Take what solace you can in the knowledge that you will not be here to witness Zendikar's demise."
-Ob Nixilis

cards.name: Devouring Swarm
cards.text:
Flying

cards.flavor: Their arrival is heralded by the deafening hum of ten thousand wings. Their departure is marked by the silence of the dead.

cards.name: Doomed Dissenter

cards.flavor: There is only one fate left to those banished from the God-Pharaoh's city.

• Dread Presence deals 2 damage to any target and you gain 2 life.
cards.flavor: It beckons silently, waiting in the darkness.

cards.name: Dread Rider
cards.text: {1}{B}, {T}, Exile a creature card from your graveyard: Target opponent loses 3 life.
cards.flavor:
"What kind of monstrous grave robber leaves the treasures, but takes the bodies?"
-Fjall, Beskir elder

cards.name: Dread Slaver

cards.flavor: Half a brain rules the mindless.

cards.name: Dreadhound
cards.text:
When Dreadhound enters the battlefield, mill three cards. (Put the top three cards of your library into your graveyard.)
Whenever a creature dies or a creature card is put into a graveyard from a library, each opponent loses 1 life.
cards.flavor: It herds souls toward eternal torment.

cards.name: Dune Beetle
cards.flavor: The scouring sands of Shefet polish its carapace, and the ranks of the cursed fill its belly.

cards.name: Durable Coilbug
cards.text: {4}{B}: Return Durable Coilbug from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor:
"I've seen them survive lava, trampling, and a moloch's digestive system. They just roll out and get on with their lives!"
-Gannet, Skysail zoologist

cards.name: Eaten Alive
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature or pay {3}{B}.
Exile target creature or planeswalker.
cards.flavor:
"If you hear a groaning noise in the cellar, don't investigate. Don't split up. Just lock the door and barricade it."
-Emili, guard captain

cards.flavor: With Thraben's army recalled to its city walls, outlying villages were left to fend for themselves.

cards.name: Epicure of Blood
cards.text: Whenever you gain life, each opponent loses 1 life.
cards.flavor: "Fleshy, with just a hint of leather. A fine vintage."

cards.name: Eviscerate
cards.text: Destroy target creature.
cards.flavor:
"Fear the dark if you must, but don't mistake sunlight for safety."
-Josu Vess

cards.name: Exsanguinate
cards.text: Each opponent loses X life. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
cards.flavor: Vampires don't consider patience a virtue nor gluttony a sin.

cards.name: Falkenrath Noble
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever Falkenrath Noble or another creature dies, target player loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
cards.flavor: "I often think on how excited they must feel to be chosen as my prey."

cards.name: Fetid Imp
cards.text:
Flying
{B}: Fetid Imp gains deathtouch until end of turn. (Any amount of damage it deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)

cards.name: Fungal Infection
cards.text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn. Create a 1/1 green Saproling creature token.
cards.flavor: To thallids, the whole world is just a pile of mulch to grow saprolings in.

cards.name: Gavony Unhallowed
cards.text: Whenever another creature you control dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Gavony Unhallowed.
cards.flavor:
"We entered the church in search of solace, but it became clear we wouldn't find it there."
-Grete, Order of Saint Traft

cards.name: Ghoulraiser

cards.flavor:
"Come. Bring your brothers. Tonight, you feast on living flesh."
-Jadar, ghoulcaller of Nephalia

cards.name: Gnawing Zombie
cards.text: {1}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Target player loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
cards.flavor: On still nights you can hear its rotted teeth grinding tirelessly on scavenged bones.

Flying

{3}{B}, Exile a creature card from your graveyard: Create a 2/2 black Zombie creature token.

cards.text:
Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
Whenever Graveblade Marauder deals combat damage to a player, that player loses life equal to the number of creature cards in your graveyard.

cards.flavor:
"Innistrad's ghoulcallers are talented enough, but let me show you what someone with real power can create."
-Liliana Vess

cards.name: Gravedigger
cards.text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: A full coffin is like a full coffer-both are attractive to thieves.

cards.name: Hooded Assassin
cards.text:

• Put a +1/+1 counter on Hooded Assassin.
• Destroy target creature that was dealt damage this turn.

cards.name: Ill-Gotten Inheritance
cards.text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, Ill-Gotten Inheritance deals 1 damage to each opponent and you gain 1 life.
{5}{B}, Sacrifice Ill-Gotten Inheritance: It deals 4 damage to target opponent and you gain 4 life.
cards.flavor: "The suffering of others is not my concern."

cards.name: Inner Demon
cards.text:
Enchant creature

When Inner Demon enters the battlefield, all non-Demon creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.

cards.name: Kalastria Nightwatch
cards.text: Whenever you gain life, Kalastria Nightwatch gains flying until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Kalitas may have returned to mindless servitude beneath the Eldrazi, but we say never again."
-Drana, Kalastria bloodchief

cards.name: Karfell Kennel-Master

cards.name: Kothophed, Soul Hoarder
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever a permanent owned by another player is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
cards.flavor: "I will be your most demanding master, Liliana. But I have great things in mind for you."

cards.name: Kraul Swarm
cards.text:
Flying
{2}{B}, Discard a creature card: Return Kraul Swarm from your graveyard to your hand.
cards.flavor: The hive has a long memory. It knows how every member ever died, and to whom it owes the grudge.

cards.name: Liliana, Death's Majesty
cards.text:
[+1]: Create a 2/2 black Zombie creature token. Mill two cards.
[−3]: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. That creature is a black Zombie in addition to its other colors and types.
[−7]: Destroy all non-Zombie creatures.

cards.name: Liliana's Elite
cards.text: Liliana's Elite gets +1/+1 for each creature card in your graveyard.
cards.flavor:
"You have to admit, Gideon-he has great form."
-Liliana Vess

cards.name: Liliana's Mastery
cards.text:
Zombies you control get +1/+1.
When Liliana's Mastery enters the battlefield, create two 2/2 black Zombie creature tokens.
cards.flavor: "There are so many of them. It seems they've just been waiting for someone to serve."

cards.name: Liliana's Steward
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice Liliana's Steward: Target opponent discards a card. Activate only as a sorcery.
cards.flavor: Servants at Vess Manor are chosen for their strong work ethic and respectful demeanor. Being alive is not required.

cards.name: Lurking Deadeye
cards.text:
Flash
When Lurking Deadeye enters the battlefield, destroy target creature that was dealt damage this turn.
cards.flavor: "There's no roar so mighty that it can't be silenced."

cards.name: Maalfeld Twins
cards.text: When Maalfeld Twins dies, create two 2/2 black Zombie creature tokens.
cards.flavor:
"Who am I to break up a family?"
-Gisa the Mad

cards.name: Marauding Blight-Priest
cards.text: Whenever you gain life, each opponent loses 1 life.
cards.flavor: "The vampires never had gods. We followed our bloodchiefs. Now they are gone. What is left? Destruction and death, my friends. That is enough."

cards.name: Marauding Boneslasher
cards.text: Marauding Boneslasher can't block unless you control another Zombie.
cards.flavor: With the Hekma destroyed, the wandering dead that sought entrance to Naktamun had free rein to lay waste to the city.

cards.name: Massacre Wurm
cards.text:
When Massacre Wurm enters the battlefield, creatures your opponents control get -2/-2 until end of turn.
Whenever a creature an opponent controls dies, that player loses 2 life.

cards.name: Mire Blight
cards.text:
Enchant creature
When enchanted creature is dealt damage, destroy it.
cards.flavor:
"Is there anything in Guul Draz that doesn't suck the life out of you?"
-Tarsa, Sea Gate sell-sword

cards.name: Mire Triton
cards.text:
Deathtouch
When Mire Triton enters the battlefield, mill two cards and you gain 2 life.
cards.flavor: Caught between life and death, between land and sea, between thought and oblivion.

cards.name: Moment of Craving
cards.text: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn. You gain 2 life.
cards.flavor: "The time of condemnation is at hand. Dusk washes over the world, and I consign you to eternal darkness!"

cards.name: Moodmark Painter
cards.text: Undergrowth - When Moodmark Painter enters the battlefield, target creature gains menace and gets +X/+0 until end of turn, where X is the number of creature cards in your graveyard. (It can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)

cards.name: Necromancer's Stockpile
cards.text: {1}{B}, Discard a creature card: Draw a card. If the discarded card was a Zombie card, create a tapped 2/2 black Zombie creature token.
cards.flavor: The experiments decided to perform some research of their own.

cards.name: Necrotic Wound
cards.text: Undergrowth - Target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn, where X is the number of creature cards in your graveyard. If that creature would die this turn, exile it instead.
cards.flavor: The assassins of the Ochran distill toxins from the remains of their previous victims.

cards.name: Nested Ghoul
cards.text: Whenever a source deals damage to Nested Ghoul, create a 2/2 black Phyrexian Zombie creature token.
cards.flavor:
"The chest cavity is cleared of useless meat. I know just what to do with the space."
-Gyed, Vault Priest

cards.name: Nirkana Assassin
cards.text: Whenever you gain life, Nirkana Assassin gains deathtouch until end of turn. (Any amount of damage it deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
cards.flavor: Nirkana assassins craft incurable concoctions by mixing basilisk marrow and deathwillow sap with the vital fluids of a dozen other poisonous species.

Whenever an opponent draws a card, Ob Nixilis, the Hate-Twisted deals 1 damage to that player.
[−2]: Destroy target creature. Its controller draws two cards.

cards.name: Ob Nixilis's Cruelty
cards.text: Target creature gets -5/-5 until end of turn. If that creature would die this turn, exile it instead.
cards.flavor: Trapped on Ravnica with no affection for either side, Ob Nixilis sought gratification in random acts of torment.

cards.name: Ophiomancer
cards.text: At the beginning of each upkeep, if you control no Snakes, create a 1/1 black Snake creature token with deathtouch.
cards.flavor:
"There are dark, ancient arts that fascinate even me."
-Sorin Markov

cards.name: Oversold Cemetery

cards.name: Phyrexian Debaser
cards.text:
Flying
{T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Debaser: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"The second stage of the illness: high fever and severe infectiousness."
-Phyrexian progress notes

cards.name: Pit Keeper

cards.flavor: "The undead are not 'awakened.' They are evicted when there is no room left in the pit for more bodies."

cards.name: Plague Spitter

When Plague Spitter dies, Plague Spitter deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.

cards.name: Priest of the Blood Rite
cards.text:
When Priest of the Blood Rite enters the battlefield, create a 5/5 black Demon creature token with flying.
At the beginning of your upkeep, you lose 2 life.
cards.flavor: Some will sacrifice everything for but a taste of power.

cards.name: Reaper from the Abyss
cards.text:
Flying
Morbid - At the beginning of each end step, if a creature died this turn, destroy target non-Demon creature.
cards.flavor: "Avacyn has deserted you. I welcome your devotion in her stead."

cards.name: Reave Soul
cards.text: Destroy target creature with power 3 or less.
cards.flavor:
"I was not convinced you had a soul until I saw it for myself."
-Liliana Vess

cards.name: Returned Reveler
cards.text: When Returned Reveler dies, each player mills three cards.
cards.flavor: The flesh is dead and the life forgotten, but old habits persist.

cards.name: Revenant
cards.text:
Flying
Revenant's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creature cards in your graveyard.
cards.flavor:
"Not again."
-Hans

cards.name: Ruthless Disposal
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card and sacrifice a creature.

cards.flavor:
"Do try to pull your weight, Geralf. I feel like I'm doing everything."
-Ghoulcaller Gisa

cards.name: Seizan, Perverter of Truth
cards.text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player loses 2 life and draws two cards.
cards.flavor:
"If you would taste the wisdom of the oni, be prepared to salt it with your blood."
-Kiku, Night's Flower

cards.name: Shadowborn Demon
cards.text:
Flying
When Shadowborn Demon enters the battlefield, destroy target non-Demon creature.
At the beginning of your upkeep, if there are fewer than six creature cards in your graveyard, sacrifice a creature.

cards.name: Shambling Ghoul
cards.text: Shambling Ghoul enters the battlefield tapped.
cards.flavor: Once he gets up and going, he will forever shamble on.

cards.name: Sinuous Vermin
cards.text:
{3}{B}{B}: Monstrosity 3. (If this creature isn't monstrous, put three +1/+1 counters on it and it becomes monstrous.)
As long as Sinuous Vermin is monstrous, it has menace. (It can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)

cards.name: Skirsdag High Priest
cards.text: Morbid - {T}, Tap two untapped creatures you control: Create a 5/5 black Demon creature token with flying. Activate only if a creature died this turn.
cards.flavor: "Thraben's pleas fall on deaf ears. Ours do not."

cards.name: Skirsdag Supplicant
cards.text: {B}, {T}, Discard a card: Each player loses 2 life.
cards.flavor:
"I can no longer stand by as these Skirsdag infiltrators rot the church from within. Even the Lunarch Council is compromised. What a fool I've been."
-Odric

cards.name: Sling-Gang Lieutenant
cards.text:
When Sling-Gang Lieutenant enters the battlefield, create two 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
Sacrifice a Goblin: Target player loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.
cards.flavor: Freshly promoted to "first rock," Zaz was eager to make an impact.

cards.name: Soulcage Fiend
cards.text: When Soulcage Fiend dies, each player loses 3 life.
cards.flavor: Vowing to free the souls of her children, Kastinne followed the tormentors into the ghastly network of caves below Stensia.

cards.name: Spark Reaper
cards.text: {3}, Sacrifice a creature or planeswalker: You gain 1 life and draw a card.
cards.flavor:
"I know they're unstoppable fighters created to harvest souls-it's just they're so rude about it."
-Kaya

cards.name: Stitcher's Supplier
cards.text: When Stitcher's Supplier enters the battlefield or dies, mill three cards.
cards.flavor: No part goes to waste.

cards.name: Strangling Spores
cards.text: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Imagine a thousand tiny mushrooms cropping up within your lungs.

cards.name: Syr Konrad, the Grim
cards.text:
Whenever another creature dies, or a creature card is put into a graveyard from anywhere other than the battlefield, or a creature card leaves your graveyard, Syr Konrad, the Grim deals 1 damage to each opponent.
{1}{B}: Each player mills a card.

cards.name: Takenuma Bleeder
cards.text: Whenever Takenuma Bleeder attacks or blocks, you lose 1 life if you don't control a Demon.
cards.flavor: "I prefer to weave my magic through oni blood, but yours will do in a pinch."

cards.name: Tivash, Gloom Summoner
cards.text:
Lifelink
At the beginning of your end step, if you gained life this turn, you may pay X life, where X is the amount of life you gained this turn. If you do, create an X/X black Demon creature token with flying.

cards.name: Tormented Soul
cards.text: Tormented Soul can't block and can't be blocked.
cards.flavor: Those who raged most bitterly at the world in life are cursed to roam the nether realms in death.

cards.name: Tragic Slip
cards.text:
Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
Morbid - That creature gets -13/-13 until end of turn instead if a creature died this turn.
cards.flavor: Linger on death's door and risk being invited in.

cards.name: Triskaidekaphobia
cards.text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, choose one -
• Each player with exactly 13 life loses the game, then each player gains 1 life.
• Each player with exactly 13 life loses the game, then each player loses 1 life.

cards.name: Typhoid Rats
cards.text: Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
cards.flavor: Kidnappers caught in Havengul are given two choices: languish in prison or become rat catchers. The smart ones go to prison.

cards.name: Ulcerate
cards.text: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn. You lose 3 life.
cards.flavor:
"If it were merely lethal, that would be sufficient. The art, however, is in maximizing the suffering it causes."
-Liliana Vess

cards.name: Undead Augur
cards.text: Whenever Undead Augur or another Zombie you control dies, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
cards.flavor:
"To see past the veil of death, cross it."
-The Red Book of Mezdrithalik

cards.name: Vampire Envoy
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever Vampire Envoy becomes tapped, you gain 1 life.
cards.flavor: "Zendikar will fight until it has bled its last."

cards.name: Vampiric Rites
cards.text: {1}{B}, Sacrifice a creature: You gain 1 life and draw a card.
cards.flavor: Scions of the Markov line take particular pleasure in the perversion of humans' holy rituals.

cards.name: Vermin Gorger
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice another creature: Each opponent loses 2 life and you gain 2 life.
cards.flavor:
"Once, vampires ruled this world, commanding the fear and respect that befit our noble blood. Have we truly sunk so low?"
-Sorin Markov

cards.name: Village Rites
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Draw two cards.
cards.flavor: The Skelle raise scorn poles in conquered villages-cursed totems of wood and bone that sap survivors of physical strength and the will to fight back.

cards.name: Vito, Thorn of the Dusk Rose
cards.text:
Whenever you gain life, target opponent loses that much life.
{3}{B}{B}: Creatures you control gain lifelink until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "Through the blood of the wicked, we shall be redeemed. Let us pray."

cards.name: Wailing Ghoul
cards.text: When Wailing Ghoul enters the battlefield, mill two cards.
cards.flavor:
"Don't worry, sweet brother. Help is on the way."
-Ghoulcaller Gisa

cards.name: Wicked Guardian
cards.text: When Wicked Guardian enters the battlefield, you may have it deal 2 damage to another creature you control. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Some are born to greatness. You were born to scrub greatness's floors."

cards.name: Witch's Cauldron
cards.text: {1}{B}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: You gain 1 life and draw a card.
cards.flavor: The best recipes start with reliable cookware.

cards.name: Yargle, Glutton of Urborg
cards.flavor: When Belzenlok's lieutenant Yar-Kul grew too ambitious, the Demonlord transformed him into a maggot. The frog that ate the maggot grew and grew, until a ravenous spirit burst from its body.

cards.name: Act on Impulse
cards.text: Exile the top three cards of your library. Until end of turn, you may play cards exiled this way. (If you cast a spell this way, you still pay its costs. You can play a land this way only if you have an available land play remaining.)
cards.flavor: "You don't want to know what happens after I put on the goggles."

cards.name: Arms Dealer
cards.text: {1}{R}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Arms Dealer deals 4 damage to target creature.
cards.flavor:
"Guaranteed to leave your enemies sufficiently stabbed, bitten, cleaved, or exploded."
-Grezkrick's Emporium motto

cards.name: Axgard Cavalry
cards.text: {T}: Target creature gains haste until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
Riding the goat
-Dwarven expression meaning
"a foolhardy act of bravery"

cards.name: Banefire
cards.text:
Banefire deals X damage to any target.
If X is 5 or more, this spell can't be countered and the damage can't be prevented.
cards.flavor: For Sarkhan Vol, the dragon is the purest expression of life's savage splendor.

cards.name: Barrage Ogre
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice an artifact: Barrage Ogre deals 2 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: The elves had devised countless strategies to combat Memnarch's war machines, but they had no idea what to do when one was thrown at them.

cards.name: Battle Squadron
cards.text:
Flying
Battle Squadron's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creatures you control.
cards.flavor: The goblins made an unruly pile with military precision.

cards.name: Big Score
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card.
Draw two cards and create two Treasure tokens. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: "Unimaginable riches? I assure you, I have a vivid imagination."

cards.name: Blaze
cards.text: Blaze deals X damage to any target.
cards.flavor: Fire never dies alone.

cards.name: Blisterspit Gremlin
cards.text:
{1}, {T}: Blisterspit Gremlin deals 1 damage to each opponent.
Whenever you cast a noncreature spell, untap Blisterspit Gremlin.
cards.flavor:
"Ah, we have a critic."
-Orthion, Lavabrink captain

cards.name: Blood Aspirant
cards.text:
Whenever you sacrifice a permanent, put a +1/+1 counter on Blood Aspirant.
{1}{R}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature or enchantment: Blood Aspirant deals 1 damage to target creature. That creature can't block this turn.
cards.flavor: It's a small step from revel to bloodbath.

cards.name: Bloodhaze Wolverine
cards.text: Whenever you draw your second card each turn, Bloodhaze Wolverine gets +1/+1 and gains first strike until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Build a moat. If we're lucky, it can't swim."
-Syr Branigan, knight of Ardenvale

cards.name: Bogardan Dragonheart
cards.text: Sacrifice another creature: Until end of turn, Bogardan Dragonheart becomes a Dragon with base power and toughness 4/4, flying, and haste.
cards.flavor: A hunger to soar must be sated.

cards.name: Bolt Hound
cards.text:
Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
Whenever Bolt Hound attacks, other creatures you control get +1/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Its spark is worse than its bite.

cards.name: Borderland Marauder
cards.text: Whenever Borderland Marauder attacks, it gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Though she is rightly feared, there are relatively few tales of her deeds in battle, for few survive her raids.

cards.name: Brazen Freebooter
cards.text: When Brazen Freebooter enters the battlefield, create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: Finders, keepers.

cards.name: Brazen Wolves
cards.text: Whenever Brazen Wolves attacks, it gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: With fewer patrols about, Kessig's roads have become prime hunting grounds.

cards.name: Burn Bright
cards.text: Creatures you control get +2/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"From a great bonfire at the dawn of time, the first Gruul kindled their rage. The same flame burns in you."
-Kroshkar, Gruul shaman

cards.name: Captain Lannery Storm
cards.text:
Haste
Whenever Captain Lannery Storm attacks, create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
Whenever you sacrifice a Treasure, Captain Lannery Storm gets +1/+0 until end of turn.

cards.name: Catalyst Elemental
cards.text: Sacrifice Catalyst Elemental: Add {R}{R}.
cards.flavor: As the hyperstormic generator crept past redline, a being emerged from the arc.

cards.name: Chandra, Flame's Fury
cards.text:
[+1]: Chandra, Flame's Fury deals 2 damage to any target.
[−2]: Chandra, Flame's Fury deals 4 damage to target creature and 2 damage to that creature's controller.
[−8]: Chandra, Flame's Fury deals 10 damage to target player and each creature that player controls.

cards.name: Chandra's Magmutt
cards.text: {T}: Chandra's Magmutt deals 1 damage to target player or planeswalker.
cards.flavor:
"Is it purebred? No, but it's pure fire."
-Chandra Nalaar

cards.name: Chandra's Pyreling
cards.text: Whenever a source you control deals noncombat damage to an opponent, Chandra's Pyreling gets +1/+0 and gains double strike until end of turn. (It deals both first-strike and regular combat damage.)
cards.flavor:
"I think Chandra just wanted something to blame random scorch marks on."
-Jace Beleren

cards.name: Chandra's Pyrohelix
cards.text: Chandra's Pyrohelix deals 2 damage divided as you choose among one or two targets.
cards.flavor:
"Now that I've dealt with your little toys, I can focus on the real problem: you."
-Chandra Nalaar, to Dovin Baan

cards.name: Chandra's Spitfire
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever an opponent is dealt noncombat damage, Chandra's Spitfire gets +3/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "I've lit most everything on fire-trees, rocks, even the water. Now it's time to burn the clouds."

cards.name: Coalhauler Swine
cards.text: Whenever Coalhauler Swine is dealt damage, it deals that much damage to each player.
cards.flavor: Nothing stops industry in Ravnica-certainly not the safety of its workers.

cards.name: Cone of Flame
cards.text: Cone of Flame deals 1 damage to any target, 2 damage to another target, and 3 damage to a third target.

cards.name: Cyclops Electromancer
cards.text: When Cyclops Electromancer enters the battlefield, it deals X damage to target creature an opponent controls, where X is the number of instant and sorcery cards in your graveyard.
cards.flavor: Every storm has an eye.

cards.name: Dance with Devils
cards.text: Create two 1/1 red Devil creature tokens. They have "When this creature dies, it deals 1 damage to any target."
cards.flavor: Devils sow chaos and reap panic.

cards.name: Deem Worthy
cards.text:
Deem Worthy deals 7 damage to target creature.
Cycling {3}{R} ({3}{R}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
When you cycle Deem Worthy, you may have it deal 2 damage to target creature.

cards.name: Destructive Tampering
cards.text:
Choose one -
• Destroy target artifact.
• Creatures without flying can't block this turn.
cards.flavor:
"I don't think they'll appreciate my . . . adjustments."
-Karavin, renegade saboteur

cards.name: Dragon Egg
cards.text:
Defender
When Dragon Egg dies, create a 2/2 red Dragon creature token with flying and "{R}: This creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn."
cards.flavor: Dragon birth lairs are littered with treasure to entice the young from their eggs.

cards.name: Dragon Fodder
cards.text: Create two 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
cards.flavor: Atarka goblins meet their demise as readily as their Temur counterparts did, but usually under big, winged shadows.

cards.name: Dragonlord's Servant
cards.text: Dragon spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
cards.flavor: Atarka serving-goblins coat themselves with grease imbued with noxious herbs, hoping to discourage their ravenous masters from adding them to the meal.

cards.name: Dragonspeaker Shaman
cards.text: Dragon spells you cast cost {2} less to cast.
cards.flavor: "We speak the dragons' language of flame and rage. They speak our language of fury and honor. Together we shall weave a tale of destruction without equal."

cards.name: Electric Revelation
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card.
Draw two cards.
Flashback {3}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost and any additional costs. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Electrify
cards.text: Electrify deals 4 damage to target creature.
cards.flavor: "Some hid from the storm. I embraced it and learned its name."

cards.name: Fanatical Firebrand
cards.text:
Haste
{T}, Sacrifice Fanatical Firebrand: It deals 1 damage to any target.
cards.flavor:
"The Brazen Coalition is a firecannon pointed at our enemies. Goblins like him are the spark to its powder."
-Admiral Beckett Brass

cards.name: Fervent Strike
cards.text: Target creature gets +1/+0 and gains first strike and haste until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"The flame paints a bright wheel on the sky, then shifts into a stabbing spark. The enemy falls; the smoke of victory rises."
-"Legends of the Firedancer"

cards.name: Fiery Conclusion
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Fiery Conclusion deals 5 damage to target creature.
cards.flavor: The Boros legionnaire saw a noble sacrifice, the Rakdos thug a blazing suicide, and the Izzet alchemist an experiment gone awry.

cards.name: Fiery Intervention
cards.text:
Choose one -
• Fiery Intervention deals 5 damage to target creature.
• Destroy target artifact.
cards.flavor: Burning something is easy. Choosing a target can be more difficult.

cards.name: Firebolt
cards.text:
Firebolt deals 2 damage to any target.
Flashback {4}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
cards.flavor: "There's more where that came from!"

cards.name: Firecannon Blast
cards.text:
Firecannon Blast deals 3 damage to target creature.
Raid - Firecannon Blast deals 6 damage instead if you attacked this turn.
cards.flavor: Goblins' fearlessness and diminutive size make them the perfect cannoneers.

cards.name: Flame Lash
cards.text: Flame Lash deals 4 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: "This is just my warm-up."

cards.name: Flames of the Firebrand
cards.text: Flames of the Firebrand deals 3 damage divided as you choose among one, two, or three targets.
cards.flavor:
"You're in luck. I brought enough to share."
-Chandra Nalaar

cards.name: Frenzied Goblin
cards.text: Whenever Frenzied Goblin attacks, you may pay {R}. If you do, target creature can't block this turn.
cards.flavor: The upside to not thinking about the consequences is that you'll always surprise those who do.

cards.name: Furnace Whelp
cards.text:
Flying
{R}: Furnace Whelp gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Baby dragons can't figure out humans-if they didn't want to be killed, why were they made of meat and treasure?

cards.name: Gadrak, the Crown-Scourge
cards.text:
Flying
Gadrak, the Crown-Scourge can't attack unless you control four or more artifacts.
At the beginning of your end step, create a Treasure token for each nontoken creature that died this turn. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")

cards.name: Glint-Horn Buccaneer
cards.text:
Haste
Whenever you discard a card, Glint-Horn Buccaneer deals 1 damage to each opponent.
{1}{R}, Discard a card: Draw a card. Activate only if Glint-Horn Buccaneer is attacking.

cards.name: Go for Blood
cards.text:
Target creature you control fights target creature you don't control. (Each deals damage equal to its power to the other.)
Cycling {1} ({1}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
cards.flavor: Lukka's bond provided not only friendship, but also the most powerful weapon in his arsenal.

cards.name: Goblin Artillery
cards.text: {T}: Goblin Artillery deals 2 damage to any target and 3 damage to you.
cards.flavor: Most goblins get their turn firing the catapult, but few achieve the coveted title of Ammunition Holder.

cards.name: Goblin Grenade
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a Goblin.
Goblin Grenade deals 5 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: Don't underestimate the aerodynamic qualities of the common goblin.

cards.name: Goblin Oriflamme
cards.text: Attacking creatures you control get +1/+0.
cards.flavor:
"It was difficult to tell whether the piles of gore within their warrens were mere trash heaps, sacred altars, or warnings."
-Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

cards.name: Goblin Psychopath
cards.text: Whenever Goblin Psychopath attacks or blocks, flip a coin. If you lose the flip, the next time it would deal combat damage this turn, it deals that damage to you instead.
cards.flavor: The destruction he causes is nothing next to the chaos in his mind.

cards.name: Goblin Rabblemaster
cards.text:
Other Goblin creatures you control attack each combat if able.
At the beginning of combat on your turn, create a 1/1 red Goblin creature token with haste.
Whenever Goblin Rabblemaster attacks, it gets +1/+0 until end of turn for each other attacking Goblin.

cards.name: Goblin Rally
cards.text: Create four 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
cards.flavor: You don't so much hire goblins as put ideas in their heads.

cards.name: Goblin Trailblazer
cards.text: Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
cards.flavor:
"Why are we following the goblin? Can he even read that map?"
-Daphne Vail, Diremore first mate

cards.name: Goblin Warchief
cards.text:
Goblin spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
Goblins you control have haste.
cards.flavor: Not since the days of Pashalik Mons have the Rundvelt goblins been so united or effective.

cards.name: Goldhound
cards.text:
First strike
Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
{T}, Sacrifice Goldhound: Add one mana of any color.
cards.flavor: The staccato clatter of its metal claws on pavement is unmistakable.

cards.name: Goldspan Dragon
cards.text:
Flying, haste
Whenever Goldspan Dragon attacks or becomes the target of a spell, create a Treasure token.
Treasures you control have "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add two mana of any one color."

cards.name: Grotag Night-Runner
cards.text: Whenever Grotag Night-Runner deals combat damage to a player, exile the top card of your library. You may play that card this turn.
cards.flavor: Naturally inquisitive and adaptable, goblins can turn their small stature to their advantage as rogues.

cards.name: Hordeling Outburst
cards.text: Create three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
cards.flavor:
"Leave no scraps, lest you attract pests."
-Mardu threat

cards.name: Hungry Flames
cards.text: Hungry Flames deals 3 damage to target creature and 2 damage to target player or planeswalker.
cards.flavor: In the hold of the Heart of Kiran, Chandra answered Dovin Baan's sabotage with an explosive retort.

cards.name: Ib Halfheart, Goblin Tactician
cards.text:
Whenever another Goblin you control becomes blocked, sacrifice it. If you do, it deals 4 damage to each creature blocking it.
Sacrifice two Mountains: Create two 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
cards.flavor: "Everybody but me-CHARGE!"

cards.name: Ignite the Future
cards.text:
Exile the top three cards of your library. Until the end of your next turn, you may play those cards. If this spell was cast from a graveyard, you may play cards this way without paying their mana costs.
Flashback {7}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Immersturm Raider
cards.text: When Immersturm Raider enters the battlefield, you may discard a card. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor: The demons took no captives and claimed no spoils; they sought only to destroy.

cards.name: Impending Doom
cards.text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +3/+3 and attacks each combat if able.
When enchanted creature dies, Impending Doom deals 3 damage to that creature's controller.
cards.flavor: "Feast, for your next meal may be your last!"

cards.name: Improvised Weaponry
cards.text: Improvised Weaponry deals 2 damage to any target. Create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
cards.flavor: Anything can be a weapon if you swing it hard enough.

cards.name: Irencrag Pyromancer
cards.text: Whenever you draw your second card each turn, Irencrag Pyromancer deals 3 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: "Fear of fire is a sensible instinct. If I were you, I'd be terrified."

cards.name: Irreverent Revelers
cards.text:
When Irreverent Revelers enters the battlefield, choose one -
• Destroy target artifact.
• Irreverent Revelers gains haste until end of turn.
cards.flavor: To some satyrs, only blasphemy is sacred.

cards.name: Kargan Dragonrider
cards.text: As long as you control a Dragon, Kargan Dragonrider has flying. (It can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
cards.flavor: "Only those who give the dragons the respect they deserve may bear our title."

cards.name: Kari Zev, Skyship Raider
cards.text:
First strike, menace
Whenever Kari Zev, Skyship Raider attacks, create Ragavan, a legendary 2/1 red Monkey creature token. Ragavan enters the battlefield tapped and attacking. Exile that token at end of combat.
cards.flavor: Aboard her ship, the Dragon's Smile, Kari follows no one's rules but her own.

cards.name: Keldon Raider
cards.text: When Keldon Raider enters the battlefield, you may discard a card. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor: Keldon raiders' spoils are limited to what their colos can carry. No matter the value, the rest goes up in smoke.

cards.name: Krenko, Mob Boss
cards.text: {T}: Create X 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens, where X is the number of Goblins you control.
cards.flavor:
"He displays a perverse charisma fueled by avarice. Highly dangerous. Recommend civil sanctions."
-Agmand Sarv, Azorius hussar

cards.name: Kuldotha Flamefiend
cards.text: When Kuldotha Flamefiend enters the battlefield, you may sacrifice an artifact. If you do, Kuldotha Flamefiend deals 4 damage divided as you choose among any number of targets.

cards.name: Lathliss, Dragon Queen
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever another nontoken Dragon enters the battlefield under your control, create a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying.
{1}{R}: Dragons you control get +1/+0 until end of turn.

cards.name: Lava Serpent
cards.text:
Haste
Cycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
cards.flavor: Lavabrink's boiling moat is a deterrent for most, and a relaxing bath for one.

cards.name: Lavastep Raider
cards.text: {2}{R}: Lavastep Raider gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Goblins were first to see the potential of hedrons in the fight against the Eldrazi, for the magical stones came ready-made with pointy bits.

cards.name: Lightning Axe
cards.text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card or pay {5}.
Lightning Axe deals 5 damage to target creature.
cards.flavor: Spirits disturbed by ghoulcallers become geists driven by restless anger.

cards.name: Mad Ratter
cards.text: Whenever you draw your second card each turn, create two 1/1 black Rat creature tokens.
cards.flavor: "Gather round and tell me all from the courts and castles."

cards.name: Magmatic Channeler
cards.text:
As long as there are four or more instant and/or sorcery cards in your graveyard, Magmatic Channeler gets +3/+1.
{T}, Discard a card: Exile the top two cards of your library, then choose one of them. You may play that card this turn.

cards.name: Mardu Heart-Piercer
cards.text: Raid - When Mardu Heart-Piercer enters the battlefield, if you attacked this turn, Mardu Heart-Piercer deals 2 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: "Those who have never ridden before the wind do not know the true joy of war."

cards.name: Markov Warlord
cards.text:
Haste
When Markov Warlord enters the battlefield, up to two target creatures can't block this turn.
cards.flavor: "What use is a stake or holy symbol in the hands of a coward?"

cards.name: Mudbutton Torchrunner
cards.text: When Mudbutton Torchrunner dies, it deals 3 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: The oil sloshes against his skull as he nears his destination: the Frogtosser Games and the lighting of the Flaming Boggart.

cards.name: Muxus, Goblin Grandee
cards.text:
When Muxus, Goblin Grandee enters the battlefield, reveal the top six cards of your library. Put all Goblin creature cards with mana value 5 or less from among them onto the battlefield and the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.
